result.execSummary:
The defendant Guy Falane Osborne was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Guy Falane Osborne in court with attorney Louis Edward Epps.  Defendant Guy Falane Osborne in custody.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.
*
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 6 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 77 days time served.  Due to financial hardship, Court waived ALL COSTS, FEES AND SURCHARGES EXCEPT THE MANDATORY SURCHARGES; due paid by 4/20/16.   Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.  No contact with the victim.
